dct_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Weymouth, drift, sheet 342
dct_description_sm: Geological Survey of Great Britain (England and Wales) Great Britain. Ordnance Survey. Sheet 342 drift. Geological Survey of Great Britain. North Decimal Degree 50.6667. South Decimal Degree 50.5000. East Decimal Degree -2.1000. West Decimal Degree -2.4833. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights.Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. Depth is shown by contour interval. "Original Geological Survey on the one-inch scale, by H. W. Bristow, F.R.S. Published in 1855 on Old Series Sheets 16 & 17. Resurveyed on the six-inch scale by C. Reid (Tertiary) and A. Strahan (secondary) and published with Drift in 1896 on the one-inch scale. Colour-printed in 1904. N.W. area, Creechbarrow and notes revised by W. J. Arkell, 1937-8. Chaldon Purbeck inlier by A. H. Taitt, 1937.".
